At the moment, for all of the mentioned applications, most of the hydrogen is obtained through steam reforming of fossil fuels. In steam reforming, hydrocarbons are converted to carbon monoxide (CO) and H2, commonly known as synthesis gas or syngas, using steam at high temperature (700–1000 °C). 11(1)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
